{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":658,"text":"I want you to imagine two couples\nin the middle of 1979"},{"time":5344,"text":"on the exact same day,\nat the exact same moment,"},{"time":8637,"text":"each conceiving a baby, OK?"},{"time":10943,"text":"So two couples each conceiving one baby."},{"time":13221,"text":"Now I don't want you to spend too\nmuch time imagining the conception,"},{"time":16511,"text":"because if you do,\nyou're not going to listen to me,"},{"time":19391,"text":"so just imagine that for a moment."},{"time":21226,"text":"And in this scenario,\nI want to imagine that, in one case,"},{"time":25424,"text":"the sperm is carrying a Y chromosome,"},{"time":27616,"text":"meeting that X chromosome of the egg."},{"time":29671,"text":"And in the other case,\nthe sperm is carrying an X chromosome,"},{"time":32867,"text":"meeting the X chromosome of the egg."},{"time":35158,"text":"Both are viable; both take off."},{"time":37747,"text":"We'll come back to these people later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39819,"text":"So I wear two hats in most of what I do."},{"time":43874,"text":"As the one hat, I do history of anatomy."},{"time":47097,"text":"I'm a historian by training,\nand what I study in that case"},{"time":51000,"text":"is the way that people\nhave dealt with anatomy --"},{"time":53610,"text":"meaning human bodies, animal bodies --"},{"time":56264,"text":"how they dealt with bodily fluids,\nconcepts of bodies;"},{"time":59000,"text":"how have they thought about bodies."},{"time":61733,"text":"The other hat that I've worn\nin my work is as an activist,"},{"time":65713,"text":"as a patient advocate --"},{"time":67593,"text":"or, as I sometimes say,\nas an impatient advocate --"},{"time":70000,"text":"for people who are patients of doctors."},{"time":72261,"text":"In that case, what I've worked with\nis people who have body types"},{"time":76000,"text":"that challenge social norms."},{"time":77939,"text":"So some of what\nI've worked on, for example,"},{"time":80120,"text":"is people who are conjoined twins --"},{"time":82191,"text":"two people within one body."},{"time":84240,"text":"Some of what I've worked on\nis people who have dwarfism --"},{"time":86984,"text":"so people who are much\nshorter than typical."},{"time":89292,"text":"And a lot of what I've worked on\nis people who have atypical sex --"},{"time":93338,"text":"so people who don't have the standard male\nor the standard female body types."},{"time":97390,"text":"And as a general term,\nwe can use the term \"intersex\" for this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"Intersex comes\nin a lot of different forms."},{"time":103562,"text":"I'll just give you a few examples\nof the types of ways you can have sex"},{"time":107000,"text":"that isn't standard for male or female."},{"time":109357,"text":"So in one instance,"},{"time":111000,"text":"you can have somebody\nwho has an XY chromosomal basis,"},{"time":114460,"text":"and that SRY gene on the Y chromosome"},{"time":117000,"text":"tells the proto-gonads,\nwhich we all have in the fetal life,"},{"time":120428,"text":"to become testes."},{"time":121636,"text":"So in the fetal life,\nthose testes are pumping out testosterone."},{"time":124782,"text":"But because this individual\nlacks receptors to hear that testosterone,"},{"time":129989,"text":"the body doesn't react\nto the testosterone."},{"time":132093,"text":"And this is a syndrome called\nandrogen insensitivity syndrome."},{"time":135692,"text":"So lots of levels of testosterone,\nbut no reaction to it."},{"time":138578,"text":"As a consequence, the body develops\nmore along the female typical path."},{"time":142504,"text":"When the child is born,\nshe looks like a girl."},{"time":144806,"text":"She is a girl, she is raised as a girl."},{"time":147928,"text":"And it's often not until she hits puberty\nand she's growing and developing breasts,"},{"time":152498,"text":"but she's not getting her period,"},{"time":154101,"text":"that somebody figures\nout something's up here."},{"time":156289,"text":"And they do some tests and figure out"},{"time":158082,"text":"that, instead of having\novaries inside and a uterus,"},{"time":160583,"text":"she has testes inside,\nand she has a Y chromosome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163053,"text":"Now what's important to understand"},{"time":164768,"text":"is you may think of this\nperson as really being male,"},{"time":167280,"text":"but they're really not."},{"time":168532,"text":"Females, like males,"},{"time":170620,"text":"have in our bodies something\ncalled the adrenal glands."},{"time":173299,"text":"They're in the back of our body."},{"time":174880,"text":"And the adrenal glands make androgens,\nwhich are a masculinizing hormone."},{"time":178334,"text":"Most females like me --\nI believe myself to be a typical female --"},{"time":181459,"text":"I don't actually know\nmy chromosomal make-up,"},{"time":183642,"text":"but I think I'm probably typical --"},{"time":185351,"text":"most females like me\nare actually androgen-sensitive."},{"time":187857,"text":"We're making androgen,\nand we're responding to androgens."},{"time":190602,"text":"The consequence is that somebody like me"},{"time":192715,"text":"has actually had a brain\nexposed to more androgens"},{"time":195758,"text":"than the woman born with testes\nwho has androgen insensitivity syndrome."},{"time":199164,"text":"So sex is really complicated --"},{"time":200710,"text":"it's not just that intersex people"},{"time":202378,"text":"are in the middle\nof all the sex spectrum --"},{"time":204479,"text":"in some ways,\nthey can be all over the place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206600,"text":"Another example:"},{"time":207782,"text":"a few years ago I got a call\nfrom a man who was 19 years old,"},{"time":210711,"text":"who was born a boy, raised a boy,"},{"time":212598,"text":"had a girlfriend,\nhad sex with his girlfriend,"},{"time":215207,"text":"had a life as a guy,"},{"time":216903,"text":"and had just found out\nthat he had ovaries and a uterus inside."},{"time":220529,"text":"What he had was an extreme form"},{"time":222305,"text":"of a condition called\ncongenital adrenal hyperplasia."},{"time":225010,"text":"He had XX chromosomes,"},{"time":226960,"text":"and in the womb, his adrenal glands\nwere in such high gear"},{"time":230723,"text":"that it created, essentially,\na masculine hormonal environment."},{"time":234365,"text":"And as a consequence,\nhis genitals were masculinized,"},{"time":236927,"text":"his brain was subject to the more typical\nmasculine component of hormones."},{"time":240463,"text":"And he was born looking like a boy --\nnobody suspected anything."},{"time":243724,"text":"And it was only when he had\nreached the age of 19"},{"time":246459,"text":"that he began to have enough medical\nproblems from menstruating internally,"},{"time":250074,"text":"that doctors figured out that, in fact,\nhe was female, internally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253934,"text":"OK, so just one more quick example\nof a way you can have intersex."},{"time":257492,"text":"Some people who have XX chromosomes\ndevelop what are called ovotestis,"},{"time":261395,"text":"which is when you have ovarian tissue\nwith testicular tissue wrapped around it."},{"time":265158,"text":"And we're not exactly sure\nwhy that happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267308,"text":"So sex can come\nin lots of different varieties."},{"time":270155,"text":"The reason that children\nwith these kinds of bodies --"},{"time":275026,"text":"whether it's dwarfism,\nor it's conjoined twinning,"},{"time":277817,"text":"or it's an intersex type --"},{"time":279167,"text":"are often \"normalized\" by surgeons"},{"time":281572,"text":"is not because it actually leaves them\nbetter off in terms of physical health."},{"time":285636,"text":"In many cases, people are actually\nperfectly healthy."},{"time":288642,"text":"The reason they're often subject\nto various kinds of surgeries"},{"time":291708,"text":"is because they threaten\nour social categories."},{"time":294553,"text":"Our system has been based\ntypically on the idea"},{"time":297346,"text":"that a particular kind of anatomy\ncomes with a particular identity."},{"time":300700,"text":"So we have the concept\nthat what it means to be a woman"},{"time":303327,"text":"is to have a female identity;"},{"time":304743,"text":"what it means to be a black person\nis, allegedly, to have an African anatomy"},{"time":309000,"text":"in terms of your history."},{"time":311117,"text":"And so we have\nthis terribly simplistic idea."},{"time":314920,"text":"And when we're faced with a body"},{"time":316577,"text":"that actually presents us\nsomething quite different,"},{"time":319535,"text":"it startles us in terms\nof those categorizations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322353,"text":"So we have a lot of very romantic ideas\nin our culture about individualism."},{"time":326318,"text":"And our nation's really founded on\na very romantic concept of individualism."},{"time":329983,"text":"You can imagine how startling then it is"},{"time":331912,"text":"when you have children who are born\nwho are two people inside of one body."},{"time":336271,"text":"Where I ran into the most heat\nfrom this most recently"},{"time":340298,"text":"was last year when South African runner,\nCaster Semenya,"},{"time":343193,"text":"had her sex called into question\nat the International Games in Berlin."},{"time":346772,"text":"I had a lot of journalists\ncalling me, asking me,"},{"time":349620,"text":"\"Which is the test they're going to run"},{"time":351518,"text":"that will tell us whether or not\nCaster Semenya is male or female?\""},{"time":355000,"text":"And I had to explain to the journalists\nthere isn't such a test."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358317,"text":"In fact, we now know\nthat sex is complicated enough"},{"time":362192,"text":"that we have to admit:"},{"time":363950,"text":"Nature doesn't draw the line\nfor us between male and female,"},{"time":367663,"text":"or between male and intersex\nand female and intersex;"},{"time":370596,"text":"we actually draw that line on nature."},{"time":373192,"text":"So what we have is a sort of situation\nwhere the farther our science goes,"},{"time":377883,"text":"the more we have to admit to ourselves\nthat these categories"},{"time":380843,"text":"that we thought of as stable\nanatomical categories,"},{"time":383554,"text":"that mapped very simply\nto stable identity categories"},{"time":387245,"text":"are a lot more fuzzy than we thought."},{"time":389404,"text":"And it's not just in terms of sex."},{"time":391381,"text":"It's also in terms of race,"},{"time":393000,"text":"which turns out to be\nvastly more complicated"},{"time":395440,"text":"than our terminology has allowed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397556,"text":"As we look, we get into all sorts\nof uncomfortable areas."},{"time":400672,"text":"We look, for example, about the fact"},{"time":402525,"text":"that we share at least 95 percent\nof our DNA with chimpanzees."},{"time":406861,"text":"What are we to make of the fact"},{"time":408585,"text":"that we differ from them\nonly, really, by a few nucleotides?"},{"time":412076,"text":"And as we get farther\nand farther with our science,"},{"time":414543,"text":"we get more and more\ninto a discomforted zone,"},{"time":416756,"text":"where we have to acknowledge\nthat the simplistic categories we've had"},{"time":420065,"text":"are probably overly simplistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422663,"text":"So we're seeing this\nin all sorts of places in human life."},{"time":426298,"text":"One of the places\nwe're seeing it, for example,"},{"time":428527,"text":"in our culture,\nin the United States today,"},{"time":430565,"text":"is battles over the beginning\nof life and the end of life."},{"time":433368,"text":"We have difficult conversations"},{"time":435000,"text":"about at what point we decide\na body becomes a human,"},{"time":438163,"text":"such that it has a different\nright than a fetal life."},{"time":441152,"text":"We have very difficult\nconversations nowadays --"},{"time":443700,"text":"probably not out in the open\nas much as within medicine --"},{"time":446473,"text":"about the question\nof when somebody's dead."},{"time":448746,"text":"In the past, our ancestors\nnever had to struggle so much"},{"time":451397,"text":"with this question\nof when somebody was dead."},{"time":453523,"text":"At most, they'd stick\na feather on somebody's nose,"},{"time":455939,"text":"and if it twitched,\nthey didn't bury them yet."},{"time":458107,"text":"If it stopped twitching, you bury them."},{"time":459990,"text":"But today, we have a situation"},{"time":461450,"text":"where we want to take\nvital organs out of beings"},{"time":463785,"text":"and give them to other beings."},{"time":465393,"text":"And as a consequence,"},{"time":466876,"text":"we have to struggle\nwith this really difficult question"},{"time":469504,"text":"about who's dead,"},{"time":471163,"text":"and this leads us\nto a really difficult situation"},{"time":473532,"text":"where we don't have such simple\ncategories as we've had before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476532,"text":"Now you might think that all this\nbreaking-down of categories"},{"time":479667,"text":"would make somebody like me really happy."},{"time":481677,"text":"I'm a political progressive,\nI defend people with unusual bodies,"},{"time":484753,"text":"but I have to admit to you\nthat it makes me nervous."},{"time":487212,"text":"Understanding that these categories"},{"time":488926,"text":"are really much more unstable\nthan we thought makes me tense."},{"time":492043,"text":"It makes me tense from the point of view\nof thinking about democracy."},{"time":495320,"text":"So in order to tell you\nabout that tension,"},{"time":497500,"text":"I have to first admit to you\na huge fan of the Founding Fathers."},{"time":500641,"text":"I know they were racists,\nI know they were sexist,"},{"time":503274,"text":"but they were great."},{"time":504471,"text":"I mean, they were so brave and so bold\nand so radical in what they did,"},{"time":509609,"text":"that I find myself watching that cheesy\nmusical \"1776\" every few years,"},{"time":514103,"text":"and it's not because of the music,\nwhich is totally forgettable."},{"time":517131,"text":"It's because of what happened in 1776\nwith the Founding Fathers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520493,"text":"The Founding Fathers were,\nfor my point of view,"},{"time":522791,"text":"the original anatomical activists,"},{"time":524867,"text":"and this is why."},{"time":526496,"text":"What they rejected\nwas an anatomical concept"},{"time":529795,"text":"and replaced it with another one"},{"time":531355,"text":"that was radical and beautiful\nand held us for 200 years."},{"time":534708,"text":"So as you all recall,"},{"time":536454,"text":"what our Founding Fathers were\nrejecting was a concept of monarchy,"},{"time":539882,"text":"and the monarchy was basically based\non a very simplistic concept of anatomy."},{"time":543544,"text":"The monarchs of the old world\ndidn't have a concept of DNA,"},{"time":547207,"text":"but they did have a concept of birthright."},{"time":549364,"text":"They had a concept of blue blood."},{"time":551060,"text":"They had the idea that the people\nwho would be in political power"},{"time":554267,"text":"should be in political power\nbecause of the blood being passed down"},{"time":557468,"text":"from grandfather to father\nto son and so forth."},{"time":561794,"text":"The Founding Fathers rejected that idea,"},{"time":564186,"text":"and they replaced it\nwith a new anatomical concept,"},{"time":566861,"text":"and that concept\nwas \"all men are created equal.\""},{"time":570718,"text":"They leveled that playing field\nand decided the anatomy that mattered"},{"time":574105,"text":"was the commonality of anatomy,\nnot the difference in anatomy,"},{"time":578543,"text":"and that was a really radical thing to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581560,"text":"Now they were doing it in part"},{"time":583036,"text":"because they were part\nof an Enlightenment system"},{"time":585352,"text":"where two things were growing up together."},{"time":587385,"text":"And that was democracy growing up,"},{"time":589677,"text":"but it was also science\ngrowing up at the same time."},{"time":592766,"text":"And it's really clear, if you look\nat the history of the Founding Fathers,"},{"time":596269,"text":"a lot of them were very\ninterested in science,"},{"time":598579,"text":"and they were interested\nin the concept of a naturalistic world."},{"time":601631,"text":"They were moving away\nfrom supernatural explanations,"},{"time":604141,"text":"and they were rejecting things\nlike a supernatural concept of power,"},{"time":607402,"text":"where it transmitted because\nof a very vague concept of birthright."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611481,"text":"They were moving\ntowards a naturalistic concept."},{"time":613787,"text":"And if you look, for example,\nin the Declaration of Independence,"},{"time":616866,"text":"they talk about nature and nature's God."},{"time":619596,"text":"They don't talk about God\nand God's nature."},{"time":621809,"text":"They're talking about the power of nature\nto tell us who we are."},{"time":625736,"text":"So as part of that,\nthey were coming to us with a concept"},{"time":629000,"text":"that was about anatomical commonality."},{"time":631734,"text":"And in doing so, they were really\nsetting up in a beautiful way"},{"time":634887,"text":"the Civil Rights Movement of the future."},{"time":636824,"text":"They didn't think of it that way,\nbut they did it for us, and it was great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640389,"text":"So what happened years afterwards?"},{"time":642056,"text":"What happened was women, for example,\nwho wanted the right to vote,"},{"time":645522,"text":"took the Founding Fathers' concept\nof anatomical commonality"},{"time":648908,"text":"being more important\nthan anatomical difference"},{"time":651139,"text":"and said, \"The fact that we have\na uterus and ovaries"},{"time":653697,"text":"is not significant enough\nin terms of a difference"},{"time":656484,"text":"to mean that we shouldn't\nhave the right to vote,"},{"time":658797,"text":"the right to full citizenship,\nthe right to own property, etc.\""},{"time":662503,"text":"And women successfully argued that."},{"time":664579,"text":"Next came the successful\nCivil Rights Movement,"},{"time":667000,"text":"where we found people like Sojourner Truth"},{"time":669143,"text":"talking about, \"Ain't I a woman?\""},{"time":671436,"text":"We find men on the marching lines\nof the Civil Rights Movement"},{"time":675405,"text":"saying, \"I am a man.\""},{"time":676779,"text":"Again, people of color\nappealing to a commonality of anatomy"},{"time":681200,"text":"over a difference of anatomy,\nagain, successfully."},{"time":683914,"text":"We see the same thing\nwith the disability rights movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687292,"text":"The problem is, of course,"},{"time":689474,"text":"that, as we begin to look\nat all that commonality,"},{"time":691876,"text":"we have to begin to question\nwhy we maintain certain divisions."},{"time":695325,"text":"Mind you, I want to maintain\nsome divisions,"},{"time":698078,"text":"anatomically, in our culture."},{"time":699769,"text":"For example, I don't want to give a fish\nthe same rights as a human."},{"time":703473,"text":"I don't want to say\nwe give up entirely on anatomy."},{"time":706082,"text":"I don't want to say a five-year-old"},{"time":707773,"text":"should be allowed to consent\nto sex or consent to marry."},{"time":710428,"text":"So there are some anatomical divisions"},{"time":712419,"text":"that make sense to me\nand that I think we should retain."},{"time":715752,"text":"But the challenge is trying\nto figure out which ones they are"},{"time":718669,"text":"and why do we retain them,\nand do they have meaning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721304,"text":"So let's go back to those two beings\nconceived at the beginning of this talk."},{"time":725118,"text":"We have two beings, both conceived"},{"time":727000,"text":"in the middle of 1979\non the exact same day."},{"time":730515,"text":"Let's imagine one of them, Mary,\nis born three months prematurely,"},{"time":734289,"text":"so she's born on June 1, 1980."},{"time":736815,"text":"Henry, by contrast, is born at term,\nso he's born on March 1, 1980."},{"time":741586,"text":"Simply by virtue of the fact"},{"time":743402,"text":"that Mary was born\nprematurely three months,"},{"time":745884,"text":"she comes into all sorts of rights\nthree months earlier than Henry does --"},{"time":750150,"text":"the right to consent to sex,\nthe right to vote, the right to drink."},{"time":754389,"text":"Henry has to wait for all of that,"},{"time":756046,"text":"not because he's actually\nany different in age, biologically,"},{"time":759084,"text":"except in terms of when he was born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761989,"text":"We find other kinds of weirdness\nin terms of what their rights are."},{"time":765173,"text":"Henry, by virtue of being\nassumed to be male --"},{"time":767390,"text":"although I haven't told you\nthat he's the XY one --"},{"time":769805,"text":"by virtue of being assumed to be male\nis now liable to be drafted,"},{"time":774000,"text":"which Mary does not need to worry about."},{"time":775964,"text":"Mary, meanwhile, cannot in all the states\nhave the same right"},{"time":779761,"text":"that Henry has in all the states,"},{"time":781385,"text":"namely, the right to marry."},{"time":782891,"text":"Henry can marry, in every state, a woman,"},{"time":785679,"text":"but Mary can only marry today\nin a few states, a woman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789219,"text":"So we have these anatomical\ncategories that persist,"},{"time":792136,"text":"that are in many ways\nproblematic and questionable."},{"time":795909,"text":"And the question to me becomes:"},{"time":797654,"text":"What do we do, as our science\ngets to be so good in looking at anatomy,"},{"time":803666,"text":"that we reach the point\nwhere we have to admit"},{"time":806260,"text":"that a democracy\nthat's been based on anatomy"},{"time":809161,"text":"might start falling apart?"},{"time":811880,"text":"I don't want to give up the science,\nbut at the same time,"},{"time":814628,"text":"it feels sometimes like the science\nis coming out from under us."},{"time":817800,"text":"So where do we go?"},{"time":819829,"text":"It seems like what happens in our culture\nis a sort of pragmatic attitude:"},{"time":823934,"text":"\"We have to draw the line somewhere,\nso we will draw the line somewhere.\""},{"time":827396,"text":"But a lot of people get stuck\nin a very strange position."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830106,"text":"So for example, Texas has at one point\ndecided that what it means to marry a man"},{"time":835000,"text":"is to mean that you don't have\na Y chromosome,"},{"time":837419,"text":"and what it means to marry a woman\nmeans you have a Y chromosome."},{"time":840513,"text":"In practice they don't test people\nfor their chromosomes."},{"time":843259,"text":"But this is also very bizarre,"},{"time":844766,"text":"because of the story I told you\nat the beginning"},{"time":847110,"text":"about androgen insensitivity syndrome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":848944,"text":"If we look at one of the Founding Fathers\nof modern democracy,"},{"time":852500,"text":"Dr. Martin Luther King,"},{"time":853704,"text":"he offers us something of a solution\nin his \"I have a dream\" speech."},{"time":856931,"text":"He says we should judge people\n\"based not on the color of their skin,"},{"time":860222,"text":"but on the content of their character,\""},{"time":862117,"text":"moving beyond anatomy."},{"time":863663,"text":"And I want to say, \"Yeah, that sounds\nlike a really good idea.\""},{"time":866666,"text":"But in practice, how do you do it?"},{"time":868346,"text":"How do you judge people based\non the content of character?"},{"time":871833,"text":"I also want to point out"},{"time":873009,"text":"that I'm not sure that is how we should\ndistribute rights in terms of humans,"},{"time":876844,"text":"because, I have to admit, that there\nare some golden retrievers I know"},{"time":880171,"text":"that are probably more deserving of social\nservices than some humans I know."},{"time":883772,"text":"I also want to say there are probably\nalso some yellow Labradors that I know"},{"time":887391,"text":"that are more capable of informed,\nintelligent, mature decisions"},{"time":890438,"text":"about sexual relations\nthan some 40-year-olds that I know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893184,"text":"So how do we operationalize\nthe question of content of character?"},{"time":897386,"text":"It turns out to be really difficult."},{"time":899335,"text":"And part of me also wonders,"},{"time":900840,"text":"what if content of character"},{"time":902736,"text":"turns out to be something\nthat's scannable in the future --"},{"time":906721,"text":"able to be seen with an fMRI?"},{"time":909054,"text":"Do we really want to go there?"},{"time":911100,"text":"I'm not sure where we go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912460,"text":"What I do know is that it seems\nto be really important"},{"time":915035,"text":"to think about the idea\nof the United States being in the lead"},{"time":918002,"text":"of thinking about this issue of democracy."},{"time":920030,"text":"We've done a really good job\nstruggling with democracy,"},{"time":922765,"text":"and I think we would do\na good job in the future."},{"time":925123,"text":"We don't have a situation\nthat Iran has, for example,"},{"time":927750,"text":"where a man who's sexually\nattracted to other men"},{"time":930067,"text":"is liable to be murdered,"},{"time":931288,"text":"unless he's willing\nto submit to a sex change,"},{"time":933483,"text":"in which case he's allowed to live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935908,"text":"We don't have that kind of situation."},{"time":937723,"text":"I'm glad to say we don't have\nthe kind of situation with --"},{"time":941046,"text":"a surgeon I talked to a few years ago"},{"time":943053,"text":"who had brought over a set\nof conjoined twins"},{"time":945513,"text":"in order to separate them,\npartly to make a name for himself."},{"time":948448,"text":"But when I was on the phone with him,\nasking why he'll do this surgery --"},{"time":951922,"text":"this was a very high-risk surgery --\nhis answer was that, in this other nation,"},{"time":955672,"text":"these children were going to be treated\nvery badly, and so he had to do this."},{"time":959329,"text":"My response to him was, \"Well,\nhave you considered political asylum"},{"time":962505,"text":"instead of a separation surgery?\""},{"time":964136,"text":"The United States has offered\ntremendous possibility"},{"time":966609,"text":"for allowing people\nto be the way they are,"},{"time":969000,"text":"without having them have\nto be changed for the sake of the state."},{"time":972722,"text":"So I think we have to be in the lead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":974924,"text":"Well, just to close,\nI want to suggest to you"},{"time":977405,"text":"that I've been talking\na lot about the Fathers."},{"time":979960,"text":"And I want to think\nabout the possibilities"},{"time":982000,"text":"of what democracy might look like,\nor might have looked like,"},{"time":984929,"text":"if we had more involved the mothers."},{"time":987385,"text":"And I want to say something\na little bit radical for a feminist,"},{"time":990447,"text":"and that is that I think that there may be\ndifferent kinds of insights"},{"time":994316,"text":"that can come from different\nkinds of anatomies,"},{"time":996589,"text":"particularly when we have\npeople thinking in groups."},{"time":999235,"text":"For years, because\nI've been interested in intersex,"},{"time":1001766,"text":"I've also been interested\nin sex-difference research."},{"time":1004267,"text":"And one of the things\nthat I've been interested in"},{"time":1006644,"text":"is looking at the differences\nbetween males and females"},{"time":1009270,"text":"in terms of the way they think\nand operate in the world."},{"time":1011933,"text":"And what we know\nfrom cross-cultural studies"},{"time":1014030,"text":"is that females, on average --"},{"time":1015894,"text":"not everyone, but on average --"},{"time":1018000,"text":"are more inclined to be very attentive\nto complex social relations"},{"time":1022915,"text":"and to taking care of people"},{"time":1024517,"text":"who are, basically,\nvulnerable within the group."},{"time":1027519,"text":"And so if we think about that,"},{"time":1029750,"text":"we have an interesting situation in hands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031775,"text":"Years ago, when I was in graduate school,"},{"time":1033765,"text":"one of my graduate advisors\nwho knew I was interested in feminism --"},{"time":1036986,"text":"I considered myself\na feminist, as I still do,"},{"time":1039246,"text":"asked a really strange question."},{"time":1040819,"text":"He said, \"Tell me what's feminine\nabout feminism.\""},{"time":1043752,"text":"And I thought, \"Well, that's the dumbest\nquestion I've ever heard."},{"time":1046947,"text":"Feminism is all about undoing\nstereotypes about gender,"},{"time":1049545,"text":"so there's nothing\nfeminine about feminism.\""},{"time":1051631,"text":"But the more I thought about his question,"},{"time":1053680,"text":"the more I thought there might be\nsomething feminine about feminism."},{"time":1056922,"text":"That is to say, there might be\nsomething, on average,"},{"time":1059655,"text":"different about female\nbrains from male brains"},{"time":1062551,"text":"that makes us more attentive\nto deeply complex social relationships,"},{"time":1067639,"text":"and more attentive\nto taking care of the vulnerable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070496,"text":"So whereas the Fathers\nwere extremely attentive"},{"time":1073023,"text":"to figuring out how to protect\nindividuals from the state,"},{"time":1076858,"text":"it's possible that if we injected\nmore mothers into this concept,"},{"time":1080727,"text":"what we would have is more of a concept\nof not just how to protect,"},{"time":1084357,"text":"but how to care for each other."},{"time":1086701,"text":"And maybe that's where\nwe need to go in the future,"},{"time":1089298,"text":"when we take democracy beyond anatomy,"},{"time":1091529,"text":"is to think less about the individual body\nin terms of the identity,"},{"time":1095088,"text":"and think more about those relationships."},{"time":1097462,"text":"So that as we the people\ntry to create a more perfect union,"},{"time":1100951,"text":"we're thinking about what we do\nfor each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1103868,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105043,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}